(361, 1, '2016-11-07 11:58:03', '2016-11-07 00:58:03', 'Thank you so much for planning and for making our holiday a very smooth one.\r\n\r\nWe started out wanting grandma to have something nice to remember while she can still travel. Coming from a small country, we tend to think places with beautiful scenery are not suitable for elderly people because of accessibility. After our trip last autumn, we were amazed by the beautiful scenery and were also impressed by the flexibility that your company provided. It was even better when you were able to provide a wheelchair throughout the trip and advised us so that the entire trip was elderly-friendly. I was still a little worried before the trip because my grandmother is quite prone to falling down, but Yama-san was very helpful and caring and involved in every way.\r\n\r\nAt two-storey indoor locations, Yama-san helped us to check for elevators and even insisted on helping to push the wheelchair. During a rainy day, we were surprised that he even prepared a blanket for my grandmother! We really appreciate the care taken, such as preparing a stool to make it easier for my grandmother to get up and down the van. We were surprised that he know all the places so well without a GPS! He always tries his best to park at the most convenient spots for us. He also went beyond the itinerary to show us places which tourists would not usually visit and was very enthusiastic in sharing his vast knowledge of those places.\r\n\r\nThank you for securing rooms with good views even though it was the peak season. It means a lot to us because it''s very unlikely that we can take her for another long trip like this given her age and dementia. My grandmother loved all the rooms very much! And thanks for arranging for the bed to be brought down at the last hotel!\r\n<div>\r\n<p class="locate">Yip Jee Theng(Singaporean)</p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<p class="locate"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-113" src="http://localhost/baodao/wp-content/